        {
            "title": "Safety Assessment for De Grebbedijk: Overtopping and Piping",
            "date": {
                "start": {
                    "month": 4,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2019
                },
                "end": {
                    "month": 6,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2019
                }
            },
            "description": "A flood defense is a hydraulic structure with the primary objective to provide protection against flooding along the coast, rivers, lakes and other waterways. Failure of a flood defense causes severe damage to life and property. In this assignment, a safety assessment is carried out for de Grebbedijk against overtopping and piping failure. The current flood safety standard of the segment under assessment is 1/10,000 years.\n",
